1
00:00:11,430 --> 00:00:13,300
Jung Hee, are you all right?

2
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,830
Jung Hee, are you okay?

3
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,000
I was thinking of visiting the hospital.

4
00:00:17,770 --> 00:00:19,370
Look at all that sweat.

5
00:00:20,410 --> 00:00:21,440
Jin.

6
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:24,810
Yes?

7
00:00:25,180 --> 00:00:26,350
Are...

8
00:00:28,780 --> 00:00:30,020
Are you two...

9
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:33,590
I'm too scared to ask if they're dating.

10
00:00:34,350 --> 00:00:37,390
Since you couldn't come,
Hae Joo took your spot.

11
00:00:37,460 --> 00:00:39,530
We were just talking about...

12
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:41,030
the show today.

13
00:00:48,230 --> 00:00:49,570
This?

14
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:52,940
This is to celebrate the broadcasting show.

15
00:00:54,910 --> 00:00:56,070
Jung Hee.

16
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:59,080
- It's not like that...
- Jung Hee!

17
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:01,510
Why did you run away like that?

18
00:01:01,710 --> 00:01:03,480
What happened, Jung Hee?

19
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:05,850
- Jung Hee!
- Jung Hee!

20
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:07,790
- Wake up!
- Gosh...

21
00:01:07,890 --> 00:01:10,260
Why did you faint there?

22
00:01:10,390 --> 00:01:12,060
- Jung Hee!
- Hae Joo.

23
00:01:19,730 --> 00:01:22,300
I better get going then.

24
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:25,900
Those weren't for Jung Hee.

25
00:01:26,570 --> 00:01:28,940
We weren't talking about
the broadcasting show.

26
00:01:29,540 --> 00:01:32,980
She's sick. I felt bad
telling her the truth.

27
00:01:34,180 --> 00:01:35,850
It would have hurt her feelings.

28
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:44,160
That girl... I'll disown her.

29
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:45,890
Is she trying to drive me crazy?

30
00:01:46,260 --> 00:01:48,590
Has she lost her mind from
drinking so much water?

31
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:51,900
Why did she run off there?

32
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,370
She pulled out the expensive IV.

33
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,200
You know how much...

34
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:59,400
Jung Hee looked forward to the show.

35
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:02,210
- She was probably upset.
- What a fool.

36
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:04,710
It's just a broadcasting show.

37
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:06,450
It's not like it's her wedding day.

38
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:08,810
Why would she wait for such a stupid thing?

39
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:11,250
Keep it down. She needs rest.

40
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:12,280
Okay, I will.

41
00:02:13,020 --> 00:02:14,250
Get out.

42
00:02:15,090 --> 00:02:16,890
- Okay.
- Now!

43
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,430
Girls, wait outside.

44
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:21,990
Go on.

45
00:02:23,830 --> 00:02:25,530
They say if you have bad luck in marriage,

46
00:02:25,530 --> 00:02:28,070
you'd have bad luck with your children.

47
00:02:28,270 --> 00:02:29,570
So that's what happened.

48
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,000
I didn't know...

49
00:02:33,010 --> 00:02:34,470
Jung Hee liked Jin so much.

50
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:36,070
Yes. Jung Hee...

51
00:02:36,210 --> 00:02:39,910
was really getting on with Jin, you know.

52
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:42,850
You have no idea how much
she waited for the show.

53
00:02:42,850 --> 00:02:43,950
Right.

54
00:02:43,950 --> 00:02:47,250
She was so happy that all of the city...

55
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:49,760
would see her as Jin's girl.

56
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:53,460
This is all because of Shim Ae Sook.

57
00:02:53,460 --> 00:02:54,560
I agree.

58
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,030
Shim Ae Sook?

59
00:02:58,730 --> 00:03:02,700
Are you saying Jung Hee
didn't just fall in?

60
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:06,470
Did this Shim Ae Sook girl
push her in the water?

61
00:03:07,570 --> 00:03:08,640
Well...

62
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,640
Well?

63
00:03:11,110 --> 00:03:14,750
Is Ae Sook the daughter
of the pub at the market?

64
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:18,050
Isn't she the daughter of the woman...

65
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:19,450
that flirts with every man?

66
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:21,120
Please, the kids are here.

67
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,860
I don't care.

68
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:26,060
It's not for sure if Ae Sook did it.

69
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:29,190
It's just an assumption.

70
00:03:29,190 --> 00:03:31,560
- An assumption?
- Yes, that's right.

71
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:36,000
Fine. I'll wait until sunrise.

72
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:38,140
You girls.

73
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:41,270
I'll interrogate all of you.

74
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:44,780
I'll make sure to find the culprit.

75
00:03:45,180 --> 00:03:48,410
This isn't just about Jung Hee.

76
00:03:48,410 --> 00:03:50,420
It almost took away...

77
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:52,920
the life of a young man.

78
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:55,390
Right, I almost forgot.

79
00:03:55,650 --> 00:03:57,160
What happened to that boy?

80
00:03:57,390 --> 00:03:59,260
What a headache.

81
00:03:59,390 --> 00:04:01,390
Is he an orphan?

82
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,330
Why is it that no one came for him?

83
00:04:03,930 --> 00:04:05,860
Bong Soo says...

84
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:09,570
that his parents are traveling abroad.

85
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:12,070
- Abroad?
- Yes.

86
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:16,580
They must be rich.

87
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:18,310
He didn't want his parents to worry,

88
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:20,210
so he begged the nurse...

89
00:04:20,210 --> 00:04:22,380
not to contact his parents.

90
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:25,020
- What a good son.
- Yes.

91
00:04:25,450 --> 00:04:26,950
My goodness.

92
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,950
Now that I look closely,

93
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:30,420
he looks pretty handsome.

94
00:04:30,990 --> 00:04:33,130
He has thick eyebrows.

95
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:35,690
- Look at that big nose.
- Yes.

96
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,260
Those lips are like cherries.

97
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:43,440
You said he's in Bong Soo's class, right?

98
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:47,410
Yes. Apparently, he gets the highest marks.

99
00:04:47,410 --> 00:04:48,940
Really? What?

100
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:51,780
Is he smiling?

101
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:57,950
I was happy.

102
00:04:58,620 --> 00:05:02,420
Jung Hee, you held me so tightly.

103
00:05:02,860 --> 00:05:04,520
I was so happy.

104
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,390
I couldn't ask for anything more.

105
00:05:07,730 --> 00:05:09,430
I'd be a happy man even if I died.

106
00:05:09,860 --> 00:05:12,160
Dong Moon, can you hear me?

107
00:05:13,530 --> 00:05:14,670
I guess not.

108
00:05:15,830 --> 00:05:16,970
Could he have...

109
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:18,900
hurt his head?

110
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:20,240
No!

111
00:05:21,410 --> 00:05:22,410
What do we do?

112
00:05:23,210 --> 00:05:24,940
- Did he go crazy?
- My goodness!

113
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:26,710
What do we do?

114
00:05:33,850 --> 00:05:35,850
Are you closed?

115
00:05:36,790 --> 00:05:37,790
Hello.

116
00:05:45,330 --> 00:05:47,600
How can I help you today?

117
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:52,400
Is it a headache?

118
00:05:52,940 --> 00:05:53,940
A toothache?

119
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,040
No?

120
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,610
Then...

121
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:00,450
I need digestive medicine.

122
00:06:00,780 --> 00:06:02,610
I have an upset stomach.

123
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:05,250
Sure.

124
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:10,020
Digestive medicine...

125
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,870
Hae Joo. Can't you think it over?

126
00:06:27,810 --> 00:06:28,940
I want to go out with you.

127
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,040
Jin.

128
00:06:30,780 --> 00:06:32,850
Like I said before,

129
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:34,510
I'd prefer it...

130
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:37,650
if we could remain as friends.

131
00:06:39,020 --> 00:06:40,050
Hae Joo,

132
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:41,820
don't be like this.

133
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:43,020
I'm sorry.

134
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:44,360
Why are you...

135
00:06:53,970 --> 00:06:55,030
Hello.

136
00:06:55,030 --> 00:06:58,200
(Kim's Pharmacy)

137
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:07,450
I don't think you came to
the broadcasting show.

138
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,720
I didn't see you there, mister.

139
00:07:10,020 --> 00:07:13,150
Do you think I have time on my hands?

140
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,330
Also,

141
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:32,970
I'm not that old.

142
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,920
Okay.

143
00:07:55,030 --> 00:07:57,530
Looking at the survey results,

144
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,830
our fellow students are surprisingly...

145
00:07:58,830 --> 00:08:02,300
more worried about love than their marks.

146
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:06,100
Have you ever worried about your love life?

147
00:08:06,370 --> 00:08:07,670
I think you would have many men around you.

148
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,510
I'm not sure.

149
00:08:13,880 --> 00:08:15,610
You can be honest with us.

150
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:17,920
What about you?

151
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:19,320
Of course I have.

152
00:08:19,990 --> 00:08:21,590
I see. Were there a lot?

153
00:08:21,590 --> 00:08:24,320
- Just once.
- I think you're lying.

154
00:08:24,390 --> 00:08:25,520
No, I'm not.

155
00:08:41,410 --> 00:08:42,470
Dad's home.

156
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,940
Dad, are you...

157
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:48,180
Do you have a guest?

158
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:49,620
Pardon me.

159
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,930
Hey, Hae Joo.

160
00:09:03,530 --> 00:09:05,660
Did you see anyone outside?

161
00:09:05,830 --> 00:09:06,930
Anyone suspicious?

162
00:09:08,130 --> 00:09:11,200
- No.
- Is that so?

163
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:14,940
Who is that man?

164
00:09:14,940 --> 00:09:17,380
He's a student of mine.

165
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:21,050
Hae Joo, he's going to
stay a few days with us.

166
00:09:21,050 --> 00:09:24,820
You can't tell anyone about it. Okay?

167
00:09:25,650 --> 00:09:27,220
- Yes, Dad.
- Good.

168
00:09:28,390 --> 00:09:29,590
Get some rest.

169
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:42,570
(Yi Il Hospital)

170
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:58,520
I'm late! Why didn't the alarm...

171
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:04,460
Right.

172
00:10:07,490 --> 00:10:08,660
My head hurts.

173
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,630
Where did everyone go?

174
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,370
Are they out to eat?

175
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:16,540
(Lee Byung Sae, Bae Dong Moon)

176
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:17,800
Bae Dong Moon.

177
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:21,870
Did he get discharged already?

178
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:27,410
Excuse me, did the guy here leave?

179
00:10:27,410 --> 00:10:29,050
I wish.

180
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:30,650
His condition worsened overnight.

181
00:10:30,650 --> 00:10:32,150
We had to send him to a hospital in Seoul.

182
00:10:32,150 --> 00:10:33,150
He's worse?

183
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:34,290
Yes.

184
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:40,260
Then Dong Moon...

185
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,360
Jung Hee, I'm so glad.

186
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,400
You're alive.

187
00:10:48,130 --> 00:10:49,330
No.

188
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,100
No, Dong Moon.

189
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,310
It's my fault.

190
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:56,240
It's all my fault.

191
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:00,080
I'm sorry, Dong Moon.

192
00:11:03,780 --> 00:11:05,450
Dong Moon.

193
00:11:06,690 --> 00:11:08,420
It's my fault.

194
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:11,860
- I'm sorry, Dong Moon.
- Hey.

195
00:11:12,290 --> 00:11:14,090
You don't have to be sorry.

196
00:11:17,530 --> 00:11:19,630
I thought you were sent to Seoul.

197
00:11:19,630 --> 00:11:20,630
What?

198
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:24,270
My bed...

199
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:25,940
is over there.

200
00:11:28,370 --> 00:11:29,680
Then are you all right?

201
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:30,680
Yes.

202
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,280
I'm completely fine.

203
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:36,320
Do you know how much you startled me?

204
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,220
Were you...

205
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:41,190
worried about me?

206
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:45,920
Why did you surprise me like that?

207
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,000
Jung Hee.

208
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:51,960
Are you okay now?

209
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,400
I heard you came down
with a terrible fever.

210
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:57,240
Of course, you'd get a stomachache...

211
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,640
from drinking so much water.

212
00:12:03,140 --> 00:12:04,210
Are you okay?

213
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:06,380
Well?

214
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,650
About that, I...

215
00:12:11,650 --> 00:12:13,990
Give it back! Give it back!

216
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,520
I want it back!

217
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:16,520
Hey.

218
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:19,190
What? What do you want back?

219
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:24,760
This?

220
00:12:25,660 --> 00:12:27,630
- Whatever!
- Oh, my.

221
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:30,840
- I'm sorry. Are you okay?
- Yes.

222
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:33,010
Number three. What are you doing here?

223
00:12:33,010 --> 00:12:35,670
Your mom said to bring you some porridge.

224
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:39,280
Seeing how strong you are,
you must be all better.

225
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:42,550
Jung Hee. You can be discharged now.

226
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:48,190
Mom won't even come see me anymore?

227
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:50,660
True. It's not like I'm Bong Soo.

228
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,660
She doesn't care whether or not I die.

229
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:54,760
Don't even get me started.

230
00:12:54,890 --> 00:12:55,990
What?

231
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,700
Are you saying Ae Sook pushed Jung Hee in?

232
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:06,170
Okay.

233
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:09,540
- I'll investigate...
- Investigate?

234
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:10,880
I've already done that.

235
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,880
Forget it all. Get rid of her.

236
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:17,580
- Get rid of her?
- Expel that brat,

237
00:13:17,580 --> 00:13:19,180
Shim Ae Sook.

238
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:22,990
Well, but...

239
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,860
You see, ma'am.

240
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:27,530
Expelling a student...

241
00:13:27,530 --> 00:13:29,530
isn't all that simple.

242
00:13:29,530 --> 00:13:30,660
Fine!

243
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:33,200
If you refuse to expel her,

244
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:36,500
I'll have no choice but
to personally, myself,

245
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:39,710
send in a protest to the
vice-commissioner...

246
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:42,470
and the Minister of Education...

247
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:45,140
and right this injustice. Is that okay?

248
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:46,750
Protest?

249
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:49,280
- Fine. Do as you wish.
- Wait.

250
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:52,450
I am just too angry right now...

251
00:13:52,450 --> 00:13:53,920
that I can't breathe.

252
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,450
I'm sure.

253
00:13:55,450 --> 00:13:57,860
You have a child too, don't you?

254
00:14:06,770 --> 00:14:07,930
Something's strange.

255
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:09,640
Are you...

256
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,800
thinking about Jin again?

257
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,640
Dong Moon.

258
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:18,540
I appreciate your saving me,

259
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:21,780
but don't meddle with whom I think about.

260
00:14:22,210 --> 00:14:23,350
Got it?

261
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,560
I like you.

262
00:14:34,030 --> 00:14:35,590
That's why I care.

263
00:14:39,060 --> 00:14:40,400
- What?
- I know...

264
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,700
that Jin is the only thing
in your heart right now.

265
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:50,440
As long as you know.

266
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:52,980
I'll pretend I didn't
hear what you just said.

267
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:54,380
That's not right.

268
00:14:55,010 --> 00:14:56,420
I like you.

269
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:58,550
How could you pretend you didn't hear me?

270
00:14:58,550 --> 00:14:59,690
That's...

271
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:05,390
It's because I won't
ever like you like that.

272
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:07,360
How do you know?

273
00:15:08,360 --> 00:15:10,100
You don't know if it'll rain tomorrow...

274
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,800
or if it'll be sunny. That's life.

275
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,930
I do know.

276
00:15:12,930 --> 00:15:14,600
- You don't know.
- I do too!

277
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,630
You don't...

278
00:15:16,970 --> 00:15:18,070
know.

279
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:20,270
I do too!

280
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:24,140
That hurts. Let go. That hurts.

281
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,650
You're really smooshy.

282
00:15:26,810 --> 00:15:28,110
